The receptionist said for travel it would be best to get the PCR test which they offered. They do not have the rapid test which in any case would probably not be accepted at Indian immigration. I gave them my medical insurance information and was not charged anything then. Sharing my experience on booking tickets to India on Air bubble routes . Lufthansa in particular . My brother( in Houston) and I ( from Seattle) had to travel to Bangalore on a family emergency. He was allowed to book Houston - Amsterdam- Frankfurt - Bangalore on Lufthansa's website. But when he arrived at the airport he was told Schengen to Schengen transfers are not allowed due to Covid. This at a time when you are trying your hardest to get to India to be with a loved one before their passing. Thankfully, he was able to be re booked at the airport Houston- Chicago-Frankfurt- Bangalore. I on the other hand traveled Seattle- Washington DC- Frankfurt- Bangalore and faced no issue. We wanted to share our experience so people who may have to travel to India in a similar situation( hopefully not) are aware and plan accordingly. Do make sure to look in to Schegen travel rules before finalising travel plans. Regarding Covid related matters, we both got a Covid PCR test done a day before our travel and very thankfully got our results in emails as we landed in Bangalore. At the airport we went through a thermal scan station followed by a Pulse Oximeter check and handing over of 2 copies of self declaration form which we filled on the flight. One was kept and 1 was returned. We also showed our Negative Covid PCR results . We were not directed to self quarantije by airport authorities. Instead the apartment community our parents live in requested we self quarantine for the 14 days. This is for Bangalore only. I am not aware how other airports are handling this. Hoping this will help anyone traveling to In 1886 he peacefully surrendered and was promised by the US Army that he would live on an Apache Reservation in Arizona. \n\nInstead he was transported as a POW to a Civil war era POW camp in Florida and then to Fort Sill where he lived for the rest of his life as a POW. He died without ever seeing his beloved home in Southern Arizona and New Mexico. He is still buried at Fort Sill.\n\nI think it’s time for him to go home to the southwest and be given back to his Apache people In accordance with the  Native American Graves Protection and Repatriation Act, Pub. L. 101-601, 25 U.S.C. 3001 et seq., 104 Stat. 3048\n\nThe Army sends Soldiers home that are found far from their homes from War. 02:06:51","updated":"2022-01-06 20:43:28","type":"photo","description":"Christianity has no inherent right to exist for indigenous people in this hemisphere.\n...Survivors want us to remember where, the legacies began....\nTitle ~ “Nun Washing the Hair of a Male Student”, 1926. The boy is, possibly Lazare C. and the nun is Sister Francois, a First Aid , worker. Whether you had lice or not, we all had the ‘coal oil’ head treatment.\nGuy Indian Residential School, Sturgeon Landing, Manitoba.\n~ The first thing the nuns did was cut and wash the children’s hair as part of the school’s practice of wiping away students’ aboriginal identities began boy’s braided hair, which often had spiritual significance, was cut. For many who wore braids for cultural reasons, the only time they cut their hair is when they are grieving the loss of loved ones.\n~ “…In keeping with the promise to civilize the little pagan, they went to work and cut off my braids, which, incidentally, according to the Assiniboine traditional custom, was a token of mourning— the closer the relative, the closer the cut. After my haircut, I wondered in silence if my mother had died, as they had cut my hair close to the scalp.” ~ Daniel Kennedy, Lebret Residential School Survivor testimony. The Guy (St. Therese) Indian Residential School (Treaty 6), managed by the Oblates of Mary Immaculate of the Roman Catholic Church (Archdiocese of Keewatin-Le Pas), began operations in 1926 at Sturgeon Landing, Saskatchewan. By 1951 it was “woefully overcrowded” with a “rather serious epidemic” affecting 19 boys. On September 4, 1952, after sparks from a torch being used by maintenance staff ignited a fire in the engine room, the school burned to the ground. The school was then relocated to Manitoba. A temporary school opened in The Pas, Manitoba and a new school building opened in 1959, located in Clearwater Lake, It is the reflection of the rich heritage of the city of Lucknow – suave, sophisticated opulent with a shine of its very own inherent aura. Mostly done on cool pastel shades it is for all those who do not wish to flaunt a vey flashy or loud demeanour but still wish to show a passionately artistic side of themselves. Chikankari work is done on a variety of textile like silk, cotton, chiffon, muslin and the like. At #Colorsofredmond we have an assorted collection of chikankari work on green , white brown , gray and yellow georgette sarees, some of which exhibit exquisite embellished gota or mukaish work. पदार्थ भोजन के लिए मिलते हैं । विवेक, वृद्धि व कौशल से शत्रुओं का पराभव होता है। प्राय: शनि की अशुभ दशा से पीडित जातक सुख और शान्ति का अनुभव करते हैं ।यदि बुध अशुभ प्रभावी हो तो अपनी अंतर्दशा में जातक को शत्रु से भयभीत तथा अज्ञात पीडा से विकल रखता है । जातक इतना उद्विग्न हो जाता है कि उसे सुस्वादु भोजन और रमणीक स्थान भी रुचिकर नहीं लगता। \uD83C\uDF39यदि केतु शुभ ग्रह से युक्त या दुष्ट होकर योगकाकरक ग्रह से सम्बन्ध करता हो तो शनि महादशा में अपनी अन्तर्दशा आने पर जातक को लेशमात्र ही शुभ फल देता है। जातक का कार्य-व्यवसाय शिथिल हो जाता है तथा किए गए श्रम का पारिश्रमिक बहुत थोडा मिलता है । नौकरी से पद एवं वेतनवृद्धि में विघ्न जाते है, नीव जनों का संग करता है, भोजन की व्यवस्था दूसरों पर निर्भर रहती है , अनेक रोग घेर लेते है और पूर्चार्जित धन चिकित्सा पर व्यय हो जाता है। वायु रोग, सर्वाग शूल, जिगर-तिल्ली, कुक्षिपीड़ा एवं मन्दाग्नि रोग से देहपीड़ा मिलती है। जातक पूर्व में मिले बुध अन्तर्दशा के शुभ फलों को याद करता है। \uD83C\uDF39शुक्र की अंतर्दशा का फल : शनि देव की महादशा में उच्च राशि, स्वराशि, शुभ ग्रहयुक्त व दृष्ट एव केन्द्र व त्रिकोण में स्थित शुक्र की अंतर्दशा हो तो जातक के व्यवसाय में वृद्धि होती है तथा प्रचुर धन कमाता है। नौकरी में हो तो पदोन्नति होती है। कलाकार, नाटककार, अपनी कला के माध्यम से धन और मान अजित कर लेते है। उच्चधिकारियों का प्रिय बन उनके ह्रदय में अपना स्थान बना लेता है, किसी नवविवाहिता से प्रेम-प्रसंग बन सकता है, ग्राम-समाज में अवस्था एव स्थिति के अनुरूप आदर-सत्कार प्राप्त होता है। अशुभ शुक की अन्तर्दशा में जातक से कामवासना अत्यधिक बढ़ जाती है, पस्त्रीगमन, वेश्यागमन, रेस, सट्टा, लाटरी आदि में संचित धन व्यय कर दरिद्र हो जाता है । खाने के भी लाले पड़ जाते है । यहा तक कि अपनी क्षुघापूर्ति के लिए भिक्षा का सहारा लेता है । \uD83C\uDF39सूर्य : शनि महादशा में उच्च राशि, स्वराशि, षडवलयुक्त सूर्य की अंतर्दशा चले तो जातक वैभवपूर्ण जीवनयापन के साधन जुटा लेता है । धन-धान्य की वृद्धि और वाहन, वस्त्रालंकार तथा पशुधन प्राप्त होता है। भाषाविद इस दशाकाल में निश्चित रूप में मान-सम्मान एव धनार्जन कर लेते है । शनि और सूर्य परस्पर नैसर्गिक शत्रु हैं, इसलिए अशुभ सूर्य की दशा में जातक को घोर कष्ट सहन करने होते हैं । कठिन परिश्रम करने वाले विद्यार्थी कठिनता से उत्तीर्ण होने योग्य अंक प्राप्त कर पाते हैं, अन्यथा अनुत्तीर्ण ही होना पड़ता है। व्यर्थ में लोगों से कलह होता है, पिता से अनबन और पैतृक सम्पत्ति से वंचित होने से मन सन्तप्त होता है । काला ज्वर एवं मन्दाग्नि रोग से पीडा मिलती है । \uD83C\uDF39चन्द्रमा-शनि महादशा में उच्च राशि, स्वराशि, शुभ ग्रहों विशेषत: बृहस्पति से दुष्ट या बृहस्पति से केद्रस्थ बली चन्द्रमा की अंतर्दशा चलती है तो जातक को आरोग्य लाभ मिलता ,है सौभाग्य में वृद्धि होती है। प्रतियोगी परीक्षा में उत्तीर्ण हो उच्च पद पा लेता है, माता का विशेष और पिता का स्वल्प सुख मिलता है । स्त्री और स्थान का सुख मिलता है एव इनके कारण यश में वृद्धि होती है । सन्तानोत्पत्ति का उत्सव धूमधाम से मनाकर लाभ अर्जित करता है ,अशुभ और क्षीण चन्द्रमा की दशा Back by popular demand!! Malai kofta with Moong daal tadka. If you've been following my posts then you remember from last time that Kofta is our word for meatball. At least that's the best I can translate it. This time the kofta is vegetarian! Where are my paneer fans at?! Malai kofta is made with paneer, potatoes and a little corn starch and milk powder to act as a glue for them. They are served in a cashew-based sauce/gravy. Please have a little yogurt ready if you are spice-sensitive. I'm hearing that some people need it. Whenever Mata-rani needed a break our dad always wanted to go eat Indian food. (yes, really.)\uD83D\uDE02\uD83D\uDE02\uD83D\uDE02 There was a local place we went to that made malai kofta and my brother and I were hooked from the first time we tried it. We still make a pilgrimage to eat it together whenever we're both back home. I hope you enjoy it, I'm looking forward to having them again, and seeing you all! This dish will be served with Moong dal tadka (tempered in ghee) and Rice. (Moong dal is split green gram.) I will be able to cook for up to 12 people on Monday. The price of each plate is $15 and I accept Zelle. Please reply here with the number of plates you would like and I'll send you a direct message with details for payment and pickup.
